At its heart, the KeyMod™ system creates the potential for universal modularity between various manufacturers of accessories and accessory rails. As more options become available, new KeyMod™ accessories will attach directly to the KeyMod™ slots rather than via Picatinny rail segments, creating a lighter, cleaner, and less bulky weapon system. The BCM KMR also allows for a greater range of customization, offering an additional 4 offset mounting points between traditional 3, 6, 9, and 12:00 positions.

The BCM KMR also features a proprietary patent pending mounting, indexing and lock up system that mitigates 12:00 rail movement due to heat generated from the barrel nut.

  The KMR's propriety finish is a plasma deposition process originally developed for the Aerospace industry. title: For Sale:  Remington Model 81 Woodsmaster [SOLD]
postcontent:
First year (1936) production Model 81 rifle for sale. I thought I would try to sell it locally before moving it to Gunbroker or doing a forum sale.

The rifle for sale here has great bluing, 90% remains. The wood has some nicks but nothing major. The action is smooth as can be and the rifle groups well out to 100 yards. It has been shot/carried very little.

The Remington Model 8 was invented by John Browning and was one of the world's first successful semi-auto rifles. It is a takedown design almost like modern survival rifles. It has the same safety as the AK-47; Kalashnikov copied this from the 8/81. The 81 was the updated version introduced in 36' and made until 1950. This one is chambered in .35 Remington. The .35 is entirely a lever gun round now days but it was originally made as an intermediate cartridge of sorts for this semi rifle. I have 3 boxes of .35 Remington Core-Lokt and Hornady Lever Revolution available too. I will give you at least 20 cases of .35 for reloading for free. 

Great fun gun with collector value or a hard-hitting, fast shooting brush gun for deer or bear if you hunt in WV or NY (or other states that allow hunting with semis) at times. You simply cannot get a semi-auto chambered in .35 Remington anymore.

Thanks for reading! Let me know if you want to see any more photos.

I will trade this rifle for a Browning BLR in certain calibers; .243, 7mm-08, .270, .308.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare _ Savage Model 99 (.303 savage)
postcontent:
I have a very rare savage model 99B made in 1902 in .303 savage. Serial #227xx, This gun absolutely pristine. Shoots exactly to the point of aim and even have ammo and dies to go with. What makes this gun so rare is the characteristics of a 99B vs. other model 99's is full Octagonal barrel 26" long. Straight grip with a "Perch Belly" Steel rifle butt that is curved, schnoble tip knife edge dovetail. As you can tell in the pictures this gun is beautiful. This gun has never been drilled and tapped..

Model 99b's are rare and in this condition its even more rare. Model 99's used a rotary magazine to hold the cartridges. The rotating magazine uses a spring-loaded spool with grooves to hold the cartridges. It also has a counter to indicate how many shots are left. This guns counter works perfect and functions flawless.

The rotating magazine design allowed the rifle to be one of the first lever-action rifles to use spitzer bullets. Previous lever-action rifles used tubular magazines, which placed cartridges of ammunition end to end. Another safety feature was that upon cocking the rifle, a small pin protrudes above the top receiver to indicate the rifle is cocked and ready to fire. This design was ahead of its time. This is a very early model 99.

This is a great deer rifle or collector piece in its current refurbished condition. This gun will not disappoint. Email or text if interested 918-four02-0854. FTF in tulsa area only.
